result.execSummary:
The defendant Valentin Solis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Valentin Solis is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Valentin Solis was found guilty of Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g) [Modifiers: Distribution to Minors], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

(NOTE:  THIS JOC CONTAINS AN ERROR IN THE SENTENCE DATE.  SENTENCE DATE IS NOT 9/16/14.  IT IS 9/17/14.)

Appearances by DA Harper, Def in custody and with Atty. Angel for sentencing.  Certified Spanish interpreter Yvon Roustan provides interpretation.  DA states there's a joint recommendation for determinate sentence of 3 years with 1 year of confinement and 2 years ext. supervision. 

Joint recommendation is that the sentence be consecutive to sentence def already serving.

Court asks about ICE situation.  DA states that, in matter previously closed, def does have an ICE hold but his deportation proceedings in that matter are not until 2017.

Def addresses the Court.

Court follows the jt recommendation.  Court grants Challenge Incarceration and ERP Program eligibility.  Sentence:  36 mo in Wisconsin prison system with Dodge as reception center.  12 mo initial confinement; 2 years ext. supervision after.  Terms of ES:  provide DNA sample, have AODA and follow through recom. of assessor; no contact with A Guzman or her children or as approved by agent; pay costs and supervision fees; participate in programming as DOC seems fit.  Credit for time served:  0 days.  This sentence consecutive to any other case def serving.

Firearms prohibition info provided - felony admonishment.

Appearances by ADA Forehand, Def in custody, and Atty. Angel for sentencing after rev in 13CF20 and status in 14CF31.

Atty. Angel states that the parties have reached an agreement to resolve both cases.  Angel details the agreement, beginning with 14CF31 in which the def will plead no contest to manufacturing/delivering THC including distribution to minors for dismissal of other two counts; PSI requested; parties free to argue.  

Court conducts prelim waiver colloquy in 14CF31.  Prelim waived - Court states the charge and the possible max. penalties.  Def pleads no contest to count 1.  Colloquy on plea.  Finding of guilty.  PSI ordered.  60 days for DOC to complete.  Sep. 17 at 3:00 for sentencing.  Counts 2 and 3 dismissed.

13CF20 - counsel jointly ask for 9 months on one count and 90 days on the other, concurrent.  Court agrees and follows the recommendation for 9 months on count 1 and 90 days on count 2, concurrent with count 1.  Court notes that def to be given sentence credit for April 26 to now - 83 days.

Def is presently on an ICE hold.

No contact with ENM (dob 4/14/03).  Noin-person contact with ANG or their residence.  Bond has been amended, however, to allow contact via telephone with ANG over the Richland County Jail's recorded telephone line.
Status conference on July 17, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

DA Harper, Def in custody, and Atty. T Angel as defense counsel.  Certified Spanish interpreter Mariana Kralewski/SWITS appears by phone, sworn by the court for interpretation in this matter.  Atty. Angel states that the Defense has received an offer from the State and needs additional time to review/consider it; asks that this matter be adjourned to July 17 during the next Spanish interpreter block (notes that def has sentencing after rev case that was set for that date as well).  Court resets this matter for July 17 at 1:30.

Court notes receipt of letter from victim, requesting to have contact with def.  Court asks for DA's input on this request given the fact that the def is presently in custody.  DA requests the following limitation:  that the def and the victim have telephone contact only as the telephone at the jail is a recorded line.  AG addresses the court; asks that she and def be allowed to have in-person contact at the jail.  Court concurs with DA's suggestion re contact only via the recorded telephone line and orders that amendment to bond.  Clerk requests clarification as to the amendment and which victim it pertains to.  AG states she's only asking for the change for herself.  Court orders that the amendment only apply to AG.

Status conference scheduled for 07-17-2014 at 01:30 pm.
